My name is Edward Bloom,
and I wanna talk to you!

236
00:23:28,707 --> 00:23:31,073
Go away!

237
00:23:32,978 --> 00:23:36,038
Now, I'm not going anywhere
until you show yourself!

238
00:23:36,214 --> 00:23:39,206
I said, go away!

239
00:23:59,604 --> 00:24:02,038
Armed with the foreknowledge
of my own death...

240
00:24:02,207 --> 00:24:04,334
...I knew the giant couldn't kill me.

241
00:24:06,645 --> 00:24:09,944
All the same, I preferred to keep
my bones unbroken.

242
00:24:10,115 --> 00:24:12,106
Why are you here?

243
00:24:13,418 --> 00:24:14,908
So you can eat me.

244
00:24:15,387 --> 00:24:19,323
The town decided to send
a human sacrifice and I volunteered.

245
00:24:19,491 --> 00:24:23,086
My arms are a little stringy, but
there's some good eating in my legs.

246
00:24:23,261 --> 00:24:26,492
I mean, I'd be tempted
to eat them myself.

247
00:24:28,633 --> 00:24:30,726
So I guess, well....

248
00:24:30,902 --> 00:24:35,168
If you'd just get it over with quick,
because I'm not much for pain, really.

249
00:24:47,652 --> 00:24:51,349
Oh, come on! I can't go back!
I'm a human sacrifice!

250
00:24:51,523 --> 00:24:54,048
If I go back,
they'll think I'm a coward.

251
00:24:54,226 --> 00:24:56,820
I'd rather be dinner than a coward.

252
00:24:57,429 --> 00:24:58,657
Here.

253
00:24:59,164 --> 00:25:02,258
You can start with my hand.
It'll be an appetizer.

254
00:25:02,434 --> 00:25:06,564
I don't want to eat you.
I don't want to eat anybody.

255
00:25:06,738 --> 00:25:10,868
I just get so hungry.
I'm just too big.

256
00:25:12,043 --> 00:25:14,841
Did you ever think that
maybe you're not too big...

257
00:25:15,013 --> 00:25:17,140
...but maybe this town
is just too small?

258
00:25:17,315 --> 00:25:20,182
I've heard in real cities
there are buildings so tall...

259
00:25:20,352 --> 00:25:22,582
...you can't even see
the tops of them.

260
00:25:22,754 --> 00:25:25,245
-Really?
-Oh, I wouldn't lie to you.

261
00:25:25,423 --> 00:25:27,550
And all-you-can-eat buffets.

262
00:25:27,726 --> 00:25:30,718
-Now, you can eat a lot, can't you?
-I can.

263
00:25:30,896 --> 00:25:33,797
So why are you wasting your time
in a small town?

264
00:25:33,965 --> 00:25:37,059
You're a big man.
You should be in a big city.

265
00:25:37,235 --> 00:25:40,432
You're just trying to get me
to leave, aren't you?

266
00:25:40,739 --> 00:25:44,266
-What's your name, giant?
-Karl.

267
00:25:44,442 --> 00:25:47,878
Well, mine's Edward.
And truthfully....

268
00:25:48,046 --> 00:25:51,880
Well, I do want you to leave, Karl.
But I want to leave with you.

269
00:25:52,050 --> 00:25:54,814
I mean, you think this town
is too small for you?

270
00:25:54,986 --> 00:25:58,080
Well, it's too small for a man
of my ambition.

271
00:25:58,256 --> 00:26:01,419
So, what do you say? Join me?

272
00:26:04,629 --> 00:26:05,857
Okay.

273
00:26:07,198 --> 00:26:08,688
Okay.

274
00:26:08,967 --> 00:26:12,164
Now, first, we gotta
get you ready for the city.

275
00:26:28,920 --> 00:26:33,186
Edward Bloom, first son of Ashton...

276
00:26:33,358 --> 00:26:36,850
...it's with a heavy heart
that we see you go.

277
00:26:37,028 --> 00:26:39,690
But take with you
this key to the city...

278
00:26:39,864 --> 00:26:42,799
...and know that any time
you want to come back...

279
00:26:42,968 --> 00:26:46,028
...all our doors are open to you.

280
00:26:54,546 --> 00:26:58,573
That afternoon as I left Ashton,
everyone seemed to have advice.

281
00:26:58,750 --> 00:27:01,617
Find yourself a nice girl, now!

282
00:27:02,053 --> 00:27:05,045
Watch your pride, Edward Bloom!

283
00:27:05,256 --> 00:27:09,625
But there was one person whose
counsel I held above all others.

284
00:27:13,698 --> 00:27:16,428
She said that the biggest fish
in the river...

285
00:27:16,601 --> 00:27:19,764
...gets that way
by never being caught.

286
00:27:24,476 --> 00:27:27,843
-What'd she say?
-Beats me.

287
00:27:39,691 --> 00:27:41,522
There were two roads out of Ashton:

288
00:27:41,693 --> 00:27:44,594
A new one which was paved
and an older one that wasn't.

289
00:27:44,763 --> 00:27:46,754
People didn't use
the old one anymore...

290
00:27:46,931 --> 00:27:49,729
...and it had developed a reputation
for being haunted.

291
00:27:49,901 --> 00:27:53,098
Well, since I had no intention
of ever returning to Ashton...

292
00:27:53,271 --> 00:27:57,435
... this seemed as good a time as any
to find out what lay down that old one.

293
00:27:57,609 --> 00:28:02,342
-You know anyone who's taken it?
-That poet, Norther Winslow, did.

294
00:28:02,814 --> 00:28:05,282
He was going to Paris, France.

295
00:28:05,450 --> 00:28:08,886
I guess he liked it.
No one ever heard from him again.

296
00:28:09,120 --> 00:28:11,247
I'll tell you what.
You go the other way.

297
00:28:11,423 --> 00:28:14,984
I'll cut through here,
and I'll meet you on the far side.

298
00:28:16,194 --> 00:28:19,288
You're just trying to run away,
aren't you?

299
00:28:20,999 --> 00:28:22,227
Here.

300
00:28:23,535 --> 00:28:26,629
Just to be sure, you can take my pack.

301
00:29:05,810 --> 00:29:07,778
Why, you son of a--

302
00:29:33,738 --> 00:29:36,332
Now, there comes a point
when a reasonable man...

303
00:29:36,508 --> 00:29:41,275
...will swallow his pride and admit
that he's made a terrible mistake.

304
00:29:41,446 --> 00:29:46,383
The truth is,
I was never a reasonable man.

305
00:29:47,552 --> 00:29:50,248
And what I recall of
Sunday school was that...

306
00:29:50,421 --> 00:29:55,518
... the more difficult something is,
the more rewarding it is in the end.

307
00:30:54,786 --> 00:30:57,550
Friend! Welcome to you!

308
00:30:57,989 --> 00:31:00,981
-What's your name?
-Edward Bloom.

309
00:31:02,093 --> 00:31:05,187
-"Bloom" like a flower?
-Yes.

310
00:31:05,363 --> 00:31:09,527
Oh, here! Here you are, right here.
"Edward Bloom."

311
00:31:09,701 --> 00:31:12,033
We weren't expecting you yet.

312
00:31:12,203 --> 00:31:14,296
-You were expecting me?
-Not yet.

313
00:31:14,472 --> 00:31:19,136
-You must've taken a shortcut.
-Why, yes, I did. It almost killed me.

314
00:31:19,644 --> 00:31:23,774
Life will do that to you.
And truthfully, the long way is easier.

315
00:31:24,215 --> 00:31:27,082
-But it's longer.
-Much longer.

316
00:31:27,252 --> 00:31:30,187
And you're here now,
and that's what matters.

317
00:31:30,355 --> 00:31:31,583
What is this place?

318
00:31:31,756 --> 00:31:35,021
The town of Spectre.
Best-kept secret in Alabama!

319
00:31:35,193 --> 00:31:38,560
Now, it says here
you're from Ashton, right?

320
00:31:38,730 --> 00:31:42,063
Last person we had from Ashton
was Norther Winslow.

321
00:31:42,233 --> 00:31:44,167
The poet?
Whatever happened to him?

322
00:31:44,335 --> 00:31:48,704
He's still here. Let me buy you a drink.
I'll tell you all about it.

323
00:31:48,873 --> 00:31:50,807
Hell, I'll have him tell you!

324
00:31:50,975 --> 00:31:54,103
I have to meet somebody,
and I'm already running late.

325
00:31:54,279 --> 00:31:58,181
Now, son, I already told you.
You're early.

326
00:32:32,684 --> 00:32:35,812
Now, tell me if that isn't
the best pie you ever ate.

327
00:32:35,987 --> 00:32:37,682
It truly is.

328
00:32:42,026 --> 00:32:45,962
Well, everything tastes better here.
Even the water is sweet.

329
00:32:48,466 --> 00:32:51,731
Never gets too hot,
too cold, too humid.

330
00:32:52,236 --> 00:32:55,433
At night, the wind goes through
the trees where you'd swear...

331
00:32:55,606 --> 00:32:58,973
...there was a whole symphony
out there playing just for you.

332
00:33:02,480 --> 00:33:03,970
Hey! Jenny!

333
00:33:04,983 --> 00:33:06,780
Come back here!

334
00:33:12,490 --> 00:33:13,889
Jenny!

335
00:33:29,474 --> 00:33:31,237
Hey, I need those.

336
00:33:31,743 --> 00:33:35,110
-There is no softer ground than town.
-That almost rhymes.

337
00:33:35,279 --> 00:33:37,770
He's our poet laureate. Come on.

338
00:33:41,319 --> 00:33:44,811
I agreed to spend the afternoon,
if only to understand...

339
00:33:44,989 --> 00:33:49,858
