coon dog he had when he was a kid...

354
00:36:12,170 --> 00:36:14,661
...back from the dead.

355
00:36:18,075 --> 00:36:19,940
Oh, darn.

356
00:36:21,879 --> 00:36:24,109
-How old are you?
-Eighteen.

357
00:36:24,282 --> 00:36:28,184
I'm 8. That means when I'm 1 8,
you'll be 28.

358
00:36:28,352 --> 00:36:33,119
-And when I'm 28, you'll only be 38.
-You're pretty good at arithmetic.

359
00:36:33,291 --> 00:36:37,785
And when I'm 38, you'll be 48.
That's not much difference at all.

360
00:36:37,962 --> 00:36:40,760
Sure is a lot now, though, huh?

361
00:37:14,532 --> 00:37:17,160
Hey, Edward!

362
00:37:26,010 --> 00:37:30,071
Roses are red
Violets are blue

363
00:37:30,248 --> 00:37:32,773
I love Spectre....

364
00:37:38,522 --> 00:37:40,513
Excuse me.

365
00:37:46,697 --> 00:37:50,133
Jenny thinks you're quite a catch.
We all do.

366
00:37:50,968 --> 00:37:52,299
What?

367
00:37:52,470 --> 00:37:55,701
I said, you're quite a catch.

368
00:38:17,962 --> 00:38:19,725
I have to leave.

369
00:38:23,768 --> 00:38:25,133
Tonight.

370
00:38:25,603 --> 00:38:26,865
Why?

371
00:38:28,239 --> 00:38:30,764
This town is more than any man
could ask for.

372
00:38:30,941 --> 00:38:34,468
And if I were to end up here,
I would consider myself lucky.

373
00:38:34,645 --> 00:38:38,547
But the truth is, I'm just not ready
to end up anywhere.

374
00:38:39,150 --> 00:38:40,845
But no one's ever left.

375
00:38:42,086 --> 00:38:45,419
How are you gonna make it
without your shoes?

376
00:38:45,589 --> 00:38:48,217
Well, I suspect it will hurt. A lot.

377
00:38:52,163 --> 00:38:54,825
Now, I'm sorry, but....
Well, goodbye.

378
00:38:58,502 --> 00:39:02,165
-You won't find a better place.
-I don't expect to.

379
00:39:07,311 --> 00:39:09,336
Promise me you'll come back.

380
00:39:10,815 --> 00:39:15,616
I promise. Someday.
When I'm really supposed to.

381
00:39:46,584 --> 00:39:49,417
That night,
I reached two conclusions.

382
00:39:50,221 --> 00:39:55,249
The first was that a dangerous path
is made much worse by darkness.

383
00:39:55,426 --> 00:40:00,159
The second was that I was
hopelessly and irrevocably lost.

384
00:40:00,731 --> 00:40:03,723
These woods would become
my graveyard.

385
00:40:05,970 --> 00:40:10,873
As difficult as it was to reach Spectre,
I was fated to get there eventually.

386
00:40:11,041 --> 00:40:14,442
After all, no man can avoid
reaching the end of his life.

387
00:40:29,093 --> 00:40:33,359
And then I realized
this wasn't the end of my life.

388
00:40:33,531 --> 00:40:36,523
This isn't how I die.

389
00:40:54,018 --> 00:40:55,349
Friend.

390
00:40:55,519 --> 00:40:59,455
-What happened to your shoes?
-They kind of got ahead of me.

391
00:41:16,373 --> 00:41:19,399
I don't know if you saw it,
but Josephine had some photos...

392
00:41:19,577 --> 00:41:21,135
...in the most recent Newsweek.

393
00:41:23,681 --> 00:41:25,171
Really?

394
00:41:25,349 --> 00:41:26,680
That's just wonderful.

395
