419
00:43:30,708 --> 00:43:33,939
I was so scared,
I woke up my parents...

420
00:43:34,111 --> 00:43:38,343
...but they said it was just a dream
and to get back to bed.

421
00:43:38,515 --> 00:43:42,007
But the next morning,
my Aunt Stacy was dead.

422
00:43:42,386 --> 00:43:44,354
That's terrible.

423
00:43:44,521 --> 00:43:49,652
Terrible for her, but think about me,
young boy with that kind of power.

424
00:43:50,227 --> 00:43:54,960
Wasn't three weeks later when the
crow came back to me in a dream...

425
00:43:55,132 --> 00:43:59,831
...and said, "Your daddy's gonna die."

426
00:44:00,671 --> 00:44:02,730
I didn't know what to do.

427
00:44:03,107 --> 00:44:06,770
I finally told my father, but he said:

428
00:44:06,944 --> 00:44:12,780
"Oh, not to worry."
But I could see he was rattled.

429
00:44:12,950 --> 00:44:15,783
The next morning, he wasn't himself.

430
00:44:15,953 --> 00:44:20,549
Kept looking around, waiting for
something to drop on his head.

431
00:44:20,724 --> 00:44:25,821
Because the crow didn't say how it
was gonna happen, just those words:

432
00:44:25,996 --> 00:44:28,226
"Your daddy's gonna die."

433
00:44:28,832 --> 00:44:34,737
Well, he left home early
and was gone a long time.

434
00:44:34,905 --> 00:44:37,635
When he finally came back,
he looked terrible...

435
00:44:37,808 --> 00:44:41,073
...Iike he was waiting
for the ax to fall all day.

436
00:44:42,112 --> 00:44:43,875
He said to my mother:

437
00:44:44,048 --> 00:44:47,814
"I've just had the worst day of my life."

438
00:44:47,985 --> 00:44:51,978
"You think you've had a bad day?"
she said.

439
00:44:52,156 --> 00:44:57,287
"This morning, the milkman
dropped dead on the porch."

440
00:44:59,430 --> 00:45:03,628
